  "format": "The 25-for-25 countdown reaches No. 11, and Sean Fennessey and Amanda Dobbins spend it on the Scorsese entry: 'The Wolf of Wall Street,' the movie they both think they ranked too low. They get into the DiCaprio-financed $100 million shoot, the 180-minute excess and whether it endorses what it shows, the 30-plus needle drops, and where the Jordan Belfort performance lands in DiCaprio's career.",
